The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	New Delhi: The BCCI secretary N. Srinivasan said on Tuesday that he found Lalit Modis reply to the three showcause notices, that had been slapped on him, unacceptable. He said his observations have been forwarded to the affiliated units and would seek ratification at the SGM on July 3.        
	Calcutta: Uncapped Usman Khawaja Tuesday was included in the 14-member Australia squad for the Test series against Pakistan in England, according to a CA media release.    
	The Squad: Ricky Ponting (c), Michael Clarke, Doug Bollinger, Brad Haddin, Ryan Harris, Nathan Hauritz, Ben Hilfenhaus, Mike Hussey, Mitchell Johnson, Simon Katich, Usman Khawaja, Marcus North, Steven Smith and Shane Watson.        
	 Calcutta: East Bengal beat Eastern Railway by 81 runs to enter the semis of the P. Sen Trophy.     
	Brief scores: East Bengal 298/6 (Shib Sagar Singh 96 n.o). Eastern Railway 217 in 43.3 ovs (Nilkantha Das 2/40). EB won by 81 runs.        
	Calcutta: Bengal beat Chandigarh 2-1 to set up a semis clash with Uttarakhand in the 47th Junior National Football Championship Tuesday.     
